On Fridays there is always a huge crowd gathering to offer the prayers.

Although the Masjid committee has done a lot to facilitate all the necessities but still the design of the mosque and the accessibilities are lacking.

It's usually we see in crowded and less developed places.

The reason for that is the ignorance of the Muslims towards the masjid fundings.

They spent a very less on this, even their monthly cigarettes  Tambakhu and Pan budgets are more than four times higher than their contributions to the mosques .

In this locality this is the only Sunni mosque needs a great attention of the local Muslims.

featured_reviews.review_id:
In Kharghar the existence of this Sunni Mosque is a great mercy of the Allah- The Merciful.

Whether locals or outsiders whoever comes here to pray , definitely its peaceful atmosphere gives a great feeling of happiness.

It's greeneries and plenty of space with trees out side the mosque let not anyone feel hassles in its shades.

It has also a Muslim cemetery ( burial ground ) which covers around 70% of its space. Rest of the 30% space is for the masjid.

The Masjid Management committee has been doing a great job. They have provided air conditioners in the main hall of the mosque .

Facility for Wudhu (ablution) & Toilet is satisfactory.

There is a plenty of space for parking available on the roadside.

Three Congregational prayer for Jumah take place here due to the huge crowd on Fridays.

The timing for the 1st Juma prayer is 1:15 Pm for 2nd 1:45 pm and for 3rd and last is 02:15pm. ( kindly cross check with the mosque management for accuracy).

On Fridays you can also find street food stalls outside the mosque, your favourite chicken biryani, Pulav, Khichda, Cutlets, Mango Milk Shakes ( in summer to quench your thirst) etc. are there.

If want to do some charity, there are many needy ones available. So keep some money while leaving to the mosque for donations.

There is a Christian cemetery and a Crematorium situated side by side as well.

Actually CIDCO has allotted lands to facilitate funeral related activities for the Muslims, Christian and Hindu Communities.

Plz like this review and ask if something left to mention or you want to know more about this place.

Wassalam !!!

2019: I reached Khargar railway station, and had to pick up an auto.

I named a nearby landmark (a hospital), but no auto-driver was willing to go with Share   (Rs 10) to the location.
In the end, hired a personal auto (Rs 40 approx) and reached the landmark. While getting off the ride, I asked the driver what to do next time to avail Share ride from the station, and he said that I should get off at NAURANG.

While in the ride, I observed the city; definitely well-developed. Felt as if I'm in the West or something. Although, in such well-off places, people seem to lose their senses regarding how to dress well. llh lmst`n

The Masjid is quite small, but well made. Alhumdulillah.

May the bless the Imam - - very nice to meet him lHmd llh.

While going back, I couldn't find auto from the surrounding area. Had to go Naurang and hire one on fare.

That's all. Almost.
The Masjid is temporary on rent, because the real masjid is under construction, and it needs funds. So please help the cause as well!

Edit 2021: The Masjid has been shifted to the new building, wllh lHmd!
